President Obama will be delivering remarks at an event announcing a national program to improve fuel efficiency and reduce carbon pollution for cars and light-duty trucks for Model Years 2017 to 2025. The event will take place at the Walter E. Washington Convention Center in Washington, D.C. and will be attended by Transportation Secretary Ray LaHood, Environmental Protection Agency Administrator Lisa Jackson, auto company executives, and UAW President Bob King. Thirteen auto companies, including Ford, GM, Chrysler, BMW, Honda, Hyundai, Jaguar/Land Rover, Kia, Mazda, Mitsubishi, Nissan, Toyota, and Volvo, will have representatives at the event. The President will also speak to an audience consisting of representatives from the auto companies, UAW employees, environmental leaders, union representatives, and Members of Congress. Advanced technology vehicles, such as electric and hybrid cars, will be displayed at the event.